# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Confidential / personal data — MUST NEVER be committed.
# The de-identification originals live OUTSIDE this folder
# (mpa_paper/_CONFIDENTIAL_originals_DO_NOT_UPLOAD/); these patterns are a guard
# in case the repository is ever initialised higher up the tree.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
_CONFIDENTIAL_originals_DO_NOT_UPLOAD/
**/_CONFIDENTIAL_*/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Run logs (leak local machine paths) and session scratch.
# Logs are regenerated by run.do on each run.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
code/logs/
*.log
*.log.txt
*.smcl
.Rhistory
.RData
.Rproj.user/
*.gph.lock

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Figures are shipped as PNG only; PDFs are not redistributed.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
results/**/*.pdf

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS / Office junk
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
~$*.docx
~$*.xlsx
~$*.xls

# NOTE (deviation from the Haiyan package): code/00_deidentify.do IS committed
# here. It documents exactly which identifier columns were dropped (no values)
# and is referenced in the README for auditability. The de-identified raw oTree
# CSVs and the de-identified Discussions workbook in data/raw/Game/ ARE committed.
